{{Spelling bee | name = 29th National Geographic Bee <!-- Commented out: | image = NationalGeographicBeeOfficialLogo.png --> | caption = | date = May 15–17, 2017 | location = [[Washington, D.C.]] | winner = Pranay Varada | age = 14 | residence = [[Irving, Texas]] | word = | contestants = 54 | moderator = | Preceded by = [[28th National Geographic Bee]] | Followed by = [[30th National Geographic Bee]] }} The '''29th''' annual '''[[National Geographic Bee]]''' was held in [[Washington, D.C.|Washington]], [[District of Columbia|D.C.]] It was sponsored by the [[National Geographic Society]]. The State Bees were held on March 31, 2017, where the 54 finalists were determined.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalgeographic.com/geobee/|title=National Geographic Bee|publisher=National Geographic Society|accessdate=19 Feb 2017}}</ref> The 2017 Champion, Pranay Varada, received a $50,000 college scholarship, a lifetime membership to the National Geographic Society, and an all-expenses-paid Lindblad expedition for two to the [[Galápagos Islands]] aboard the new National Geographic Endeavour ll.<ref>https://www.nationalgeographic.org/newsroom/top-geography-students-set-sights-on-2017-national-geographic-bee-champion-title-and-85000-in-college-scholarships/</ref>
