[[File:Edan lepucki 2014.jpg|thumb|right|Lepucki at the 2014 Texas Book Festival]] '''Edan Lepucki''' is an American [[novelist]] notable for her [[debut novel]], ''[[California (novel)|California]]'', which rose to prominence as a result of a public dispute between comedian [[Stephen Colbert]] and online publisher [[Amazon.com|Amazon]].<ref name=globe>{{cite news|last1=Simon|first1=Clea|title='California' by Edan Lepucki|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/books/2014/07/17/book-review-california-eden-lepucki/6VVBgYqc1Q9Bz7xtaRkTyM/story.html|work=[[Boston Globe]]|date=17 July 2014}}</ref>
==Early life== Edan Lepucki grew up in [[Los Angeles, California]] and graduated from [[Oberlin College]] and the [[University of Iowa]] Writers’ Workshop.<ref name=nyt2>{{cite news|last1=Barnes|first1=Brooks|title=Winner in the Amazon War|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/03/business/media/edan-lepuckis-novel-california-gets-a-boost-from-colbert.html|work=[[New York Times]]|date=2 July 2014}}</ref>
==Career== Lepucki's [[debut novel]], ''[[California (novel)|California]]'', rose to prominence as a result of a public dispute between comedian [[Stephen Colbert]] and online publisher [[Amazon.com|Amazon]],<ref name=globe/> which arose when Colbert urged his viewers on two successive nights of [[The Colbert Report|his talk show]] to pre-order copies of the novel from his own publisher, the [[Hachette Book Group USA|Hachette Book Group]].
The novel was subsequently reviewed by national newspapers including the ''[[Boston Globe]]'', ''[[Washington Post]]'', the ''[[New York Times]]''<ref name=nyt2/> the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', and others.<ref name=ow>{{cite news|last1=Young|first1=Jessica|title=2014 Summer Guide: Beach Reads|url=http://orlandoweekly.com/news/beach-reads-1.1693544?pgno=1|work=[[Orlando Weekly]]|date=28 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=NYP>{{cite news|author=[[Susannah Cahalan]]|title=The 29 best books of the summer|url=https://nypost.com/2014/05/24/the-29-best-books-of-the-summer/|work=[[New York Post]]|date=24 May 2014}}</ref> The ''New York Times'' suggested Lepucki had, in effect, "won the literary Lotto".<ref name=globe/> The ''[[San Jose Mercury News]]'' described Lepucki as a "terrific writer."<ref name=twsSanJoseMN>Georgia Rowe, 07/21/2014, ''San Jose Mercury News'', [http://www.mercurynews.com/entertainment/ci_26189037/books-by-bay-edan-lepuckis-california-deserves-its Books by the Bay: Edan Lepucki's 'California' deserves its Stephen Colbert 'bump'], Accessed July 22, 2014, "'California' deftly weaves the terrifying strands of what we already know with what we can only imagine"</ref> According to one report, Lepucki signed 10,000 copies of her novel over the span of three days.<ref name=bia>{{cite news|last1=Stone|first1=Madeline|title=The Awesome Story Of How Stephen Colbert Helped A Debut Author Win Against Amazon|url=http://www.businessinsider.com.au/edan-lepucki-california-book-beating-amazon-2014-7|work=Business Insider Australia|date=10 July 2014}}</ref> Lepucki is an instructor with the [[UCLA Extension Writers' Program]].<ref name=twsUCLAXtension>[http://writers.uclaextension.edu/instructors/lepucki-edan/ Edan Lepucki], Accessed July 22, 2014</ref> Her fiction has appeared in ''McSweeney's'', ''Los Angeles Times Magazine'', ''Narrative Magazine'', ''Meridian'' and elsewhere.<ref name=twsUCLAXtension/>
