{{Infobox person | name = Heiner Lauterbach | image =Heiner Lauterbach by Stuart Mentiply.jpg | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1953|4|10|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Cologne]] ([[Germany]]) | occupation = Actor | yearsactive = 1976 — present | homepage = }}
'''Heiner Lauterbach''' (born 10 April 1953) is a [[Germany|German]] actor.
== Life and work == Heiner Lauterbach was married to German actress [[Katja Flint]] who is the mother of his son Oscar (*1988). Later he had a relationship with [[Jenny Elvers]]. Since 7 September 2001 he has been married to [[Viktoria Skaf]]. They have two children: Maya (*2002) and Vito (*2007). Heiner Lauterbach is the dubbed German voice for several American actors. Among others he has dubbed [[Richard Gere]], [[Jack Nicholson]] and [[Christopher Reeve]].
