'''Industrial Skills Qualification''' ('''ISQ''') is a post-secondary [[Vocational education|vocational]] qualification in [[Brunei]]. It is a Level 2 qualification in the country's [[Brunei Darussalam National Qualifications Framework|national qualifications framework]] and in the same level as the academic [[GCE Ordinary Level|O Level]] qualification. ISQ was introduced in 2013 and is awarded in the [[Institute of Brunei Technical Education]];<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.brudirect.com/news.php?id=12954|title=Sixth ISQ Starts Orientation for Training Batch {{!}} Brunei's No.1 News Website|website=www.brudirect.com|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref> entry into ISQ programmes is for Year 9 leavers in the current education system, the 21st Century National Education System ({{Lang-ms|Sistem Pendidikan Negara Abad Ke-21}}) or commonly known as SPN21, or Form Three leavers in pre-SPN21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/2015/02/18/post-secondary-progression-opportunities/|title=IBTE : Institute of Brunei Technical Education - Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence|last=IBTE|website=ibte.edu.bn|language=en|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref>

