{{Infobox film | name = Mike Makes His Mark | image = | caption = | director = Irving Rusinow | producer = Agrafilms, Inc. | writer = Jarvis Couillard | starring = | music = [[Norman Lloyd (composer)|Norman Lloyd]]<ref name="lloyd">McCarty, Clifford. [https://books.google.com/books?id=IK7tuydSUpQC&pg=PA194&lpg=PA19#v=onepage&q&f=false Film Composers in America: A Filmography, 1911-1970], p. 194 (2000)</ref> | cinematography = | editing = Wilkes Straley | distributor = | released = 1955 | runtime = 30 minutes, 16 mm. | country = United States | language = English | budget = | gross = }}
'''''Mike Makes His Mark''''' is a 1955 educational American film directed by Irving Rusinow and produced by Agrafilms, Inc. for the [[National Education Association]] (NEA) and state education associations.
The film tells the story of 8th grader "Mike" who wishes to drop out of school, but with help from his teacher and guidance counselor finds activities that make him interested in school, while his friend Eddie is a ditch digger.<ref name="ref1">[https://books.google.com/books?id=OiPmAAAAMAAJ&q=%22mike+makes+his+mark%22&dq=%22mike+makes+his+mark%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwies8K6osvNAhVBaT4KHVdoDzgQ6AEIJDAC The Educational Screen, Volume 35], p. 65 (1956)</ref><ref name="ref2">[https://books.google.com/books?id=n9_jAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA365&dq=%22mike+makes+his+mark%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwies8K6osvNAhVBaT4KHVdoDzgQ6AEIKDAD#v=onepage&q=%22mike%20makes%20his%20mark%22&f=false Education Films], p. 367 (1973)</ref><ref name="ref3">Wagner, Robert W. [https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2FBF02718459#page-1 Mike Makes His Mark (review)], Audiovisual communication review, December 1956, Volume 4, Issue 1, pp 64-69.</ref>
The film was the fifth in a series of NEA educational films, and it debuted at the NEA's annual convention in [[Chicago]] in July 1955.<ref name="lodi">(17 June 1955). [https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2245&dat=19550617&id=z7kzAAAAIBAJ&sjid=2u4HAAAAIBAJ&pg=3600,5503172&hl=en Mrs. Campbell to be Delegate to NEA Convention], ''Lodi News-Sentinel''</ref>
