The '''Pedagogical University''' ({{lang-pt|Universidade Pedagógica}}) is one of [[Mozambique]]'s principal [[universities]]. The name of the school is abbreviated to '''UP'''. The main campus of the school is located in Maputo. There are over 16,000 students attending the UP system.
==Campuses== UP has schools at the following locations: *[[Maputo]] *[[Beira, Mozambique|Beira]] *[[Nampula]] *[[Quelimane]] *[[Gaza Province|Gaza]] *[[Niassa]]
==Student enrollment== In 2007, Universidade Pedagogica had 31,695 contact students and 506 distance students. Most of these, 31,157, are full-time with a reported 538 part-time students. The questionnaire response also noted that three students were from SADC countries and four from other countries (excluding the SADC region).<ref>http://www.sarua.org/?q=uni_Universidade%20Pedagogica Universidade Pedagogica Retrieved 31 December 2011</ref>
